<title>USA: Harbinger files for 2.9 mln share offering.</title>
<headline>Harbinger files for 2.9 mln share offering.</headline>
<dateline>ATLANTA 1997-07-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Harbinger Corp said it filed with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission for a 2.9 million share offering, consisting of 1.8 million shares to be sold by Harbinger and 1.1 million shares to be sold by selling shareholders.</p>
<p>The selling shareholders are AXA Equity &amp; Law Assurance Society Plc, Orbis Pension Trustees Limited and Vulcan Ventures Inc.</p>
<p>The offering will be underwritten by Alex. Brown &amp; Sons Inc, Robinson-Humphrey Co Inc, Robertson Stephens &amp; Co and Interstate/Johnson Lane Corp.</p>
